{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"museum":1,"inscriptions":15},{"slug":2,"type":3,"name":4,"uri":5,"description":6,"location":7},"002","museum","Museo Archeologico Regionale di Centuripe","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/002","An excellent and comprehensive display of archaeological material from Centuripe and the surrounding area",{"settlement":8,"region":9,"country":10,"address":11,"geo":12},"Centuripe","Enna","Italy","Via Giulio Cesare, 94010 Centuripe (EN)",{"lat":13,"lon":14},37.622753,14.740806,[16,117,178,244,289,342,391,436,475,510,546,581,618,662,756,804,845],{"file":17,"uri":17,"title":18,"status":19,"editionAuthor":21,"type":22,"objectType":26,"material":30,"condition":34,"layoutDesc":36,"handNote":45,"date":60,"places":65,"geo":73,"country":10,"region":77,"settlement":8,"repository":78,"idno":79,"textLang":82,"facsimile":86,"provenance":67,"letterHeights":93,"publications":94,"zotero":100,"keywords":106,"html":116},"ISic000655","Honorific inscription for Clodia Falconilla",{"_":20},"edited",null,{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},"honorific","#function.honorific","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/69.html",{"_":27,"ana":28,"ref":29},"plaque","#object.plaque","https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},"marble","#material.stone.marble","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html",{"ana":35},"#condition.damaged",{"layout":37},{"p":38,"rs":39,"damage":43},"Five lines of Latin text, in straight alignment and shifted toward the right, with a wider left margin.The letters in the first line, which is partially legible, are of slightly greater module than those in the following lines, and are more widely spaced. The last line – of which only parts of one or more letters are preserved (perhaps an A and and the left apex of a V; an M is also possible) are preserved – appears more centered, with both left and right margins wider.",{"_":40,"ana":41,"ref":42},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":44},"text_condition.partly_illegible",{"lettering":46,"dimensions":47},"Elegant square capital letters, slightly verticalized, with serifs. The O in l. 1 is square in shape compared to the O in the other lines; A has a vertical crossbar, P has an open loop. In l. 2, a triple nexus links the letters T, R, and I, with the I rising above. In l. 4, there is spacing between the words Sosius and Priscus. Comma-shaped punctuation marks appear in ll. 1 and 3. A damaged ivy leaf appears at the end of l. 1.",[48,55],{"type":49,"l":50,"from":51,"to":52,"h":53,"unit":54},"letterHeight","Line 1-4","line1","line4","80","mm",{"type":56,"l":57,"from":51,"to":58,"h":59,"unit":54},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 5","line5","30-35",{"_":61,"notBefore":62,"notAfter":63,"evidence":64},"Early 2nd century, mother of cos. 108 CE",101,120,"prosopography",[66,70],{"_":67,"type":68,"ref":69},"Centuripae","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462153",{"_":8,"type":71,"ref":72},"modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525032",[74],[75,76],37.62336,14.74049,"Sicily",{"_":4,"role":3,"ref":5},{"_":80,"type":81},"KA0858","inventory",{"_":83,"mainLang":84,"languages":85},"Latin","la",[83],{"n":87,"url":88,"height":89,"width":90,"desc":91,"surfaceType":92},"screen","ISic000655_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-05-09","front",[],[95,95,96,97,98,99],"L'année épigraphique: revue des publications épigraphiques relatives a l'antiquité romaine., 1888-","Libertini, 1926, Centuripe","Manganaro, 1989, Iscrizioni Latine nuove e vecchie della Sicilia","Eck, 1996, Senatorische familien der kaiserzeit in der provinz Sizilien","Eck, 1996, Senatoren und senatorische Grundbesitz auf Sizilien",[101,101,102,103,104,105],"R46KDTZX","VJZRAI26","EZMBJ6GN","4HE5CIGJ","7T8K8ATA",[107,108,109,23,27,31,110,111,112,113,111,114,115,84],"isic000655","honorific inscription for clodia falconilla",{"_":20},"centuripae","centuripe","italy","sicily","museo archeologico regionale di centuripe","latin","Text encoding: Francesca Prado; edition source: autopsy Prado 2023-05-09",{"file":118,"uri":118,"title":119,"status":120,"editionAuthor":21,"type":121,"objectType":125,"material":127,"condition":128,"layoutDesc":130,"handNote":136,"date":150,"places":154,"geo":157,"country":10,"region":77,"settlement":8,"repository":159,"idno":160,"textLang":162,"facsimile":164,"provenance":67,"letterHeights":168,"publications":169,"zotero":171,"keywords":173,"html":177},"ISic000656","Honorific inscription for Sextus Pompeius Priscus",{"_":20},{"_":122,"ana":123,"ref":124},"funerary","#function.funerary","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html",{"_":27,"ana":28,"ref":126},"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},{"ana":129},"#condition.fragments.contiguous",{"layout":131},{"p":132,"rs":133,"damage":134},"Three lines of Latin text in straight alignment. Line 1 has a larger module than Line 2, and Line 2 has a larger module than Line 3. Furthermore, the lack of space in the final line resulted in a greater compression between the letters compared to the other lines.",{"_":40,"ana":41,"ref":42},{"ana":135},"text_condition.incomplete",{"lettering":137,"dimensions":138},"Elegant square capital letters, slightly verticalized, with serifs. P has an open loop; O and Q are ovoid; A has a vertical crossbar. Spacing in line 2 between the words Quir(ina) and Prisc[o]. A comma-shaped punctuation mark appears in line 1, between Q(uinto) and Pompeio.",[139,143,147],{"type":49,"l":140,"from":51,"to":141,"h":142,"unit":54},"Line 1-3","line3","10-12",{"type":56,"l":144,"from":51,"to":145,"h":146,"unit":54},"Interlineation line 1 to 2","line2","6",{"type":56,"l":148,"from":145,"to":141,"h":149,"unit":54},"Interlineation line 2 to 3","7",{"_":151,"notBefore":152,"notAfter":153,"evidence":64},"Uncle of cos. of 149 CE (?)",140,160,[155,156],{"_":67,"type":68,"ref":69},{"_":8,"type":71,"ref":72},[158],[75,76],{"_":4,"role":3,"ref":5},{"_":161,"type":81},"KA0846 + KA0850 + KA0861",{"_":83,"mainLang":84,"languages":163},[83],{"n":87,"url":165,"height":166,"width":167,"desc":91,"surfaceType":92},"ISic000656_tiled.tif","3115px","4251px",[],[95,95,96,170,97,98],"Libertini, 1953, Centuripe. Nuove indagini sulle costruzioni presso il Mulino Barbagallo. Campagna di scavo 1950-51",[101,101,102,172,103,104],"B8N2BQ9F",[174,175,176,122,27,31,110,111,112,113,111,114,115,84],"isic000656","honorific inscription for sextus pompeius priscus",{"_":20},"Text encoding: Alex Antoniou, Francesca Prado; edition source: autopsy Prado 2023-05-09",{"file":179,"uri":179,"title":180,"status":181,"editionAuthor":21,"type":182,"objectType":186,"material":187,"condition":188,"layoutDesc":189,"handNote":194,"date":212,"places":217,"geo":220,"country":10,"region":77,"settlement":8,"repository":222,"idno":223,"textLang":225,"facsimile":227,"provenance":67,"letterHeights":230,"publications":231,"zotero":235,"keywords":239,"html":243},"ISic000699","Dedication by an Augustalis",{"_":20},{"_":183,"ana":184,"ref":185},"dedication","#function.dedication","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/88.html",{"_":27,"ana":28,"ref":126},{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},{"ana":129},{"layout":190},{"p":191,"rs":192,"damage":193},"Four lines of Latin text, in straight alignment. The letters in the first two lines are of larger module than those in the other lines. The letters of l. 3 appear narrower and more compressed than the others. The inscribed field is bordered by a moulded frame. In the lower part, decorative elements are visible, including a strip or handle, and a small vessel.",{"_":40,"ana":41,"ref":42},{"ana":135},{"lettering":195,"dimensions":196},"Elegant capital letters with slight serifs. P with op